<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Global Markets Operations/Middle Office Group (GMO&amp;MO) provides controlled and efficient pre and post-trade processes in support of our Capital Markets, Corporate Investments, Corporate Treasury, Global Wealth and Investment Management, and LaSalle Global Trust Services businesses. Core functions include post confirmation, settlement and client services processes as well as assurance over data and processes used to record risk, P/L, balance sheet and financial results. The organization is aligned to products and business management:
</p>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Global Middle Office delivers control functions responsible for providing assurance over data and processes used to record risk, P/L, balance sheet and financial results in support of Global Markets, Corporate Treasury and Corporate Investments businesses</li>
	<li>Global Markets Fixed Income Operations and Client Services delivers trading, sales and syndicate support, funding, clearance, settlement, and other core operational services to the Global Markets businesses for fixed income and traded loan products, as well as the Corporate Treasury and Investment Portfolio businesses across all products. Also provides client and product reference data services across all products and regions globally</li>
	<li>Global Equity Operations delivers trading, sales and syndicate support for the Equity business in the Americas. Provides operational support for across products for Global Markets businesses in Latin America and Canada</li>
	<li>Global Markets Projects and Change Management provides quality oversight as it relates to managing operational risk, overall associate satisfaction and key strategic initiatives as well as providing efficient and effective delivery of prioritized change management initiatives</li>
	<li>Global Derivatives, Foreign Exchange, Futures and Commodities Operations provides confirmation, settlement, and customer service processes for the Global Interest Rate Derivative, Credit Derivative, Equity Derivative, Foreign Exchange, Commodity, and Futures businesses</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>
<p class="bac">
This unique program invites analysts to become expert at one or more of the functions that GMO&amp;MO perform while being exposed to our organisation via cultural, product and process training. Analysts successful after the first year will be invited to strengthen their markets or process knowledge via selection of one of a number of industry recognised Industry Qualifications (IAQ, CIMA or CFA).
</p>
<p class="bac">
Secondments are structured to develop analysts into subject matter experts by product or function (i.e. Credit Products, Rates, Currencies and Commodities, Structured Products and Equity Financial Products) and key functional areas (i.e. Client Services, Risk and Position Validation, Trade Support). There will be opportunity for secondments to be selected or changed to match the interests and skills of Analysts provided the business can accommodate this.
</p>
<p class="bac">
In addition to developing cross-functional thinking and strong technical skills, analysts also receive on-the-job training, a defined learning curriculum, participate in bi-monthly speaker seminars, and attend events with analysts and associates from across Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Candidates must have obtained or are realistically expecting to obtain a minimum 2:1 degree or equivalent. You must be able to demonstrate a combination of academic aptitude, quantitative skills, strategic and creative thinking, and excellent written and oral communication skills. Analysts will be required prioritise, multi-task and work effectively both individually and as part of a team.
</p>
<p class="bac">
Some common driving characteristics we look for:
</p>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Attention to detail</li>
	<li>Exceptional academic achievement</li>
	<li>Initiative; team focus</li>
	<li>Leadership</li>
	<li>Strategic and creative thinking capabilities</li>
	<li>Strong work ethic</li>
	<li>Strong communication skills</li>
	<li>Dedication to a career in middle office or global operations</li>
	<li>A penchant for identifying and resolving problems proactively</li>
	<li>Technology proficiency</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
As an analyst, you will begin your career at Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America with an extensive training program. The full program is a combination of classroom instruction, e-learning modules and presentations, culminating in the opportunity to earn an industry recognised qualification. Throughout the program, you&#39;ll have ample opportunities to work closely with professionals and peers throughout our organization. This is a great opportunity to build a network of colleagues from across the company that will prove to be a tremendous resource to you throughout your career.
</p>

